<refnamediv><refname>imsegkmeans</refname><refpurpose>Segment an image with OpenCV k-means.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>[labels, centers] = imsegkmeans(image, clusterCount)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input grayscale or RGB image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>clusterCount</term><listitem><para>Number of k-means clusters.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>labels</term><listitem><para>1-based label image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>centers</term><listitem><para>Cluster center values.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imsegkmeans</function> clusters pixels with OpenCV 5 k-means++ and returns a 1-based label image plus one center row per cluster.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_smarties.png"));
image = imresize(image, [120 160]);
[labels, centers] = imsegkmeans(image, 4);
segmented = imlabel2rgb(labels);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(segmented);]]></programlisting></refsection>
